2017 was a great year. I married my best friend and made Forbes 30 under 30. It honestly feels like a dream because 5 years ago… I was a total screwup. When I first got started, my business was unhealthy. The accounting and the financial sides were a mess. I let it get out of control. I think a lot of entrepreneurs do that in their first year. When the end of the year comes they’re like, "Oh, my God! I've got to clean up this massive mess.” I had an unhealthy business, but I also had an unhealthy body. I was eating poorly. I was staying up really late. I was drinking too much Red Bull. I was totally unhealthy. That was showing up in my business as well. When I decided to fix myself, my business improved, too. It's a fascinating thing. I often tell clients - "People don't have business problems, they have personal problems that reflect in their business". The opposite is also true - "People don't have business success, they have personal success that reflects in their business”. For most entrepreneurs or consultants if their business isn't making money… Or It's not moving forward or growing... They try to solve it with more tactics. More ads. New chatbot. Tweak the product. Start blogging. They believe they can just go to the business side of things and fix it, but they totally ignore their personal side. If somebody has an issue with their business, it always comes back to some personal issue in their life. If somebody isn't committed in business, this lack of commitment will often (not always) show up in other areas of their life. They won't be committed to their spouse, they won't be committed to eating healthy or following a specific routine. If there's no commitment in their business, there will be no commitment in the personal life. If you have a messy house, then you probably have a messy business. If you have a messy house, you probably have a messy mind. If you have an unhealthy body, then you probably have an unhealthy business. People try to solve business problems with pure business tactics. That's the only thing they believe will work. I can tell you that no amount of business tactics will solve a personal issue that shows up in your business. The only way to solve it is to solve the issues in your personal life as well. Over the years, Ashleigh has helped me become a better person and that has definitely reflected in my business. I can honestly say that I wouldn't be where I am today without her! I'm happy to report that I've closed her for a lifetime contract and it felt way better than having Forbes value my company at $65,000,000 or any material accomplishment. The good news? I put together a free training showing you exactly how I made this transformation. I show you how I broke the habit of being myself and how I started my business and grew it to more than $20 million. More importantly… I show you how you can do the same even faster than I did by applying methods I learned frpm my journey. You can register here for free:  I found the crown of consulting lying in the gutter, picked it up with a sword and it was mine. Whatever crown or achievement you desire is lying in the gutter too, all you have to do it pick it up and put it on.

Yesterday was an amazing journey into the past and reliving some known and  unknown moments.  Some names I had known since college, some faces only seen on Facebook or whatsapp came live yesterday. Vimi, the elegant lady in our group.  Timeless beauty is what describes her best.  Soft spoken and correct to a fault.  She has raised two great good looking children, (runs in genes I suppose).  One an entrepreneur and the younger one an aspiring model, a Miss India aspirant.  And Bina, there is always a smile on her face and what a smile! She lights up the room like a 10,000 watt bulb.  Mother of two highly intelligent daughters one in Canada and other leaving soon.  Highly successful career woman with a leadership position at leading banking solutions company. Ravika, wow. "living life on her own terms" was coined to define Ravi as lovingly called by friends.  An entrepreneur, an artist a mother all rolled in one. What a mellifluous voice she has.  Rediscovered singing very late in life otherwise by now would have been a national icon.  Where were you all my life? Indira, I have written about her in another post so will keep it short here,  but yes a gutsy woman who has come all the way from Australia to fight a property case in India courts, something which locals also fear.   And finally Francis, a revelation. I had connected to him via Facebook only. But in person, absolutely blows the mind. An international businessman who has taken his family business to another level.  A singer par excellence and an entertainer like no other I know.  Joke a minute is the moniker I would love to give him. Truly amazing how his brain work. A ladies man, has all the ladies eating out of his hand.  Must have broken quite a few hearts, I am sure. Fighting diabetes and getting better of it is no mean task. All in all it was a brilliant evening.  Mesmerizing is the word I would like to use. Hope to have many more in near future. before I forget a Hunk for hubby.
